OL,3,C'We're not ordinary, we're
OL,4,Cextraordinary' Three women on their
OL,5,Cfight for justice
OL,7,FJo, from South Warnborough in
OL,8,FHampshire, was wrongly prosecuted by
OL,9,Fthe Post Office in the Horizon IT
OL,10,Fscandal when computing errors made it
OL,11,Flook like postmasters and
OL,12,Fpostmistresses had been stealing funds.
OL,14,FAnd Shelagh has campaigned with the
OL,15,FSolent branch of what's called the
OL,16,FWASPI women. The group is fighting for
OL,17,Fjustice for women born in the 1950s
OL,18,Fwho were affected by changes to the
OL,19,FState Pension Age.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G4/21
