OL,3,C'We're not ordinary, we're
OL,4,Cextraordinary' Three women on their
OL,5,Cfight for justice
OL,7,F"People talk about ordinary people
OL,8,Ftaking on the might of the state,"
OL,9,Fsaid Shelagh, "But my view is that
OL,10,Fwe're not ordinary people. We're
OL,11,Factually extraordinary people because
OL,12,Fwe're doing this.
OL,14,F"Our situations are very different,
OL,15,Fand I wouldn't compare compare our
OL,16,Fsituation with people who've been
OL,17,Fthrough criminal prosecutions or
OL,18,Fpeople who've had contaminated blood.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/21
