OL,3,C'We're not ordinary, we're
OL,4,Cextraordinary' Three women on their
OL,5,Cfight for justice
OL,7,F"The deaths aren't on the scale of the
OL,8,Finfected blood scandal, but we've had
OL,9,Fhundreds of postmasters die, waiting
OL,10,Ffor justice," Jo added.
OL,12,F"It's the people that are so fragile,
OL,13,Fthat haven't got voices that we have
OL,14,Fto stand up and fight for."
OL,16,FShelagh said 3.8 million women were
OL,17,Faffected initially by increases to the
OL,18,Fstate pension age firstly to 65 and
OL,19,Fthen 66.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/21
