OL,3,C'We're not ordinary, we're
OL,4,Cextraordinary' Three women on their
OL,5,Cfight for justice
OL,7,FJackie was a key witness at the
OL,8,FInfected Blood Inquiry, which has
OL,9,Ftaken five years to complete.
OL,11,F"It was very traumatic having to write
OL,12,Fmy witness statement mentally," she
OL,13,Fsaid.
OL,15,F"I was pleased to attend because I had
OL,16,Fthe opportunity to speak out. I felt
OL,17,Flistened to and valued.
OL,19,F"It's probably the first time since
OL,20,Fbeing infected that that's happened to
OL,21,Fme, that I've just not been dismissed.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G9/21
