OL,3,C'We're not ordinary, we're
OL,4,Cextraordinary' Three women on their
OL,5,Cfight for justice
OL,7,F"The drama, (Mr Bates versus the Post
OL,8,FOffice, ITV) made it look like it
OL,9,Fcould happen to anybody.
OL,11,F"We were regular people, you know, not
OL,12,Faiming to set the world on fire, but
OL,13,Fwe were just shafted, and I think that
OL,14,Fresonated with the public and the fact
OL,15,Fthat we've been shouting for so long."
OL,17,FShelagh believes that the Government
OL,18,Fthought that they would 'roll over'.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/21
